      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The decline was driven primarily by a combination of economic structural shifts, such as the rise of private employers, who found it financially advantageous to avoid unionization dues. While some criticized union leadership for corruption and rigidity, these internal issues played a secondary role compared to the massive outsourcing and automation that eroded the manufacturing base where unions traditionally thrived. Ultimately, the shift towards a service-based economy with different power dynamics made collective bargaining significantly more difficult.",
